value.snippet: Mount Cairnes is a 3,060-metre mountain summit located in the Freshfield Ranges of the Canadian Rockies in British Columbia, Canada. The mountain is situated 44 km north of Golden in the Blaeberry Valley, 5.5 km east-northeast of Mount Mummery, and 3 km from the Continental Divide of. The mountain was named in 1917 after noted geologist Delorme Donaldson Cairnes of the Geological Survey of Canada from 1905 through 1917.
